Digitization may hold the key to unlocking greater value from mining operations but brings with it challenges for third-world countries in particular that could prohibit its effective utilisation. LAURA CORNISH sat down with BARRY ELLIOTT, Rockwell Automation’s global industry director for metals, mining and cement at the Rockwell Automation Fair in Philadelphia, United States late last year to discuss what important technologies offers the mining sector in Africa and how to approach concerns around its impact on employment and deployment without the necessary skills sets. Africa’s need to create employment does somewhat conflict with the mining industry’s need to become relevant within the global economy Elliott starts.